OL,3,CHeroes describe dramatic sinking car
OL,4,Crescue
OL,6,F"This very large chap, he was very,
OL,7,Fvery athletic, I could tell he was
OL,8,Fever so strong and he said I'm here to
OL,9,Fcatch you.
OL,11,F"When they let you go, I'll catch you,
OL,12,Fyou'll float. We'll all support you
OL,13,Fand we'll get you to shore.
OL,15,FRobert reflects that if it hadn't been
OL,16,Fa sunny day his sunroof would not have
OL,17,Fbeen open and the failed electrics
OL,18,Fcould have meant no escape.
